title: Propulsion Assignment
description: This assignment covers the fundamentals of rocket propulsion, including engine types, fuel chemistry, and practical applications of rocket technology.

description: This assignment focuses on the analysis of combustion processes in rocket engines, including stability and efficiency.

description: This project involves designing and optimizing rocket nozzles for specific applications, emphasizing performance and efficiency.

description: This quiz covers the principles and applications of aerodynamics, including airflow, lift and drag forces, and airfoil design.

description: This assignment focuses on the analysis of airflow patterns and fluid dynamics in aerodynamic systems.

description: This assignment involves analyzing the heating effects of aerodynamic forces on flying objects, including thermal control and heat dissipation.

description: This task involves designing spacecraft structures, including materials, load-bearing capacity, and structural integrity.

description: This exam covers the principles of systems engineering in spacecraft design, including integration, testing, and verification processes.
